reviews.review_text: - Amazingly no one has remarked on this version of the show yet; it's the best-sounding one so far, and the show itself is easily one of the greatest of the year.

It’s Fine Time To Re-Listen a Classic To my ears this is a SIGNIFICANT upgrade to the various captures of a damn fine 1978 evening at Red Rocks. OctopusRider’s 3 source  matrix is no slouch so I wasn’t expecting to be blown away by the clarity and aural imaging in doncit’s remaster. I suggest reading his notes in the Source Info section for details about how he put this beauty together.

On this recording the little things just stand out more. There’s Jerry with a prankster smirk telling Mr. Benson he’d “probably” blow him straight to hell; or Donna and Bobby cracking up during BIODTL; that smooth as fuck transition from deep Space into a kick-ass NFA like lava descending for you with a Cheshire grin;       the list goes on
